q1 -> Write a SQL query that returns each month_date, the total revenue for that month, and the month-over-month revenue growth as a percentage (rounded to 1 decimal place). The first month should show NULL for growth. Order by month_date ascending.

Sol 1 -> WITH REVENUE_1 AS
(SELECT MONTH_DATE, SUM(REVENUE) OVER(PARTITION BY MONTH_DATE ORDER BY MONTH_DATE) AS TOTAL_REVENUE
FROM MONTHLY_REVENUE)
, REVENUE_2 AS
(SELECT DISTINCT(MONTH_DATE) AS MONTHS, TOTAL_REVENUE AS NEW_REVENUE 
FROM REVENUE_1) 
, REVENUE_3 AS (SELECT MONTHS, NEW_REVENUE, LAG(NEW_REVENUE) OVER(ORDER BY MONTHS) AS OLD_REVENUE
FROM REVENUE_2)
SELECT MONTHS, NEW_REVENUE, ROUND((NEW_REVENUE-OLD_REVENUE)*100.0/OLD_REVENUE,1)
FROM REVENUE_3


